## Predicting Target Customers using Classification

### Example notebook to predict customers most likely to be positive responders to an Affinity Card loyalty program.  This notebook builds and applies classfication models (decision tree) using the SH schema data and processed inside the Oracle Autonomous Data Warehouse Cloud (ADWC).

#### By Charlie Berger

paragraphs.title: Select and view Likely and unlikely AFFINITY_CARD responsers
Interactively show customer probability to be AFFINITY_CARD responders
paragraphs.text:
%sql 
SELECT A.*, B.* FROM N1_APPLY_RESULT A, N1_TEST_DATA B WHERE PREDICTION = ${PREDICTION='1','1'|'0'} and a.CUST_ID = b.CUST_ID;

paragraphs.title: Interactive Pie Chart of likely AFFINITY_CARD responders
Select customers who above threshold probability (20%) of being likely AFFINITY_CARD responders
paragraphs.text:
%sql
-- Displays customers more than 20% likely to respond.

SELECT * from(
SELECT CUST_ID, PREDICTION_PROBABILITY(N1_CLASS_MODEL, '1'  USING A.*) prob
 FROM N1_APPLY_RESULT A)
 WHERE prob > 0.2;

paragraphs.title: Real-time prediction
paragraphs.text:
%sql
Select prediction_probability(N1_CLASS_MODEL, '1'
  USING '3' as HOUSEHOLD_SIZE, 5 as YRS_RESIDENCE, 1 as Y_BOX_GAMES)
from dual;

paragraphs.title: Interactive selection of likely Affinity_Card reponders selected by HOUSEHOLD_SIZE
